.TH NICX 1 "2025-04-25" "nicx 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
nicx \- personal Linux system toolkit by Nicolas
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nicx
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ subcommand ]
.RI [ options ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nicx
is a personal Linux system toolkit designed for use on minimal or fresh Linux
installations. It provides a unified CLI for system inspection, configuration
management, and Linux administration tasks.
.PP
The tool is self-contained, requires no runtime dependencies beyond the C++
standard library, and stores its configuration in
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
following the XDG Base Directory specification.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B system
Inspect the current system. Default subcommand is
.BR info .
.TP
.B pkg
Package management with install tracking. Detects the system package manager
automatically (yay, pacman, dnf, apt, zypper).
.TP
.B git
Git and GitHub CLI setup, authentication, and repository tracking.
.TP
.B gpg
GPG key management: generation, listing, status, export, and import.
.TP
.B pass
password-store setup and management with GPG and optional git remote sync.
.TP
.B help
Show general help, or help for a specific command when given as an argument.
.TP
.B version
Print the version string and exit.
.
.SH SYSTEM SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx system info
Display a full system overview including:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
Operating system name, ID, version, kernel, hostname, and init system
.IP \(bu
CPU model, architecture, core count, and thread count
.IP \(bu
Memory total, used, available, and swap usage
.IP \(bu
Boot mode (EFI/BIOS), bootloader detection (GRUB, systemd-boot, rEFInd)
.IP \(bu
Disk partitions with filesystem, usage, and LUKS encryption status
.RE
.
.SH PKG SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx pkg install \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR...]
Install one or more packages via the detected package manager, then save them
to the tracking list in
.IR ~/.config/nicx/packages.toml .
.TP
.B nicx pkg remove \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR...]
Uninstall packages and remove them from the tracking list.
.TP
.B nicx pkg update
Update all system packages (equivalent to \fIdnf upgrade\fR, \fIpacman -Syu\fR, etc.).
.TP
.B nicx pkg search \fIterm\fR
Search available packages in the configured repositories.
.TP
.B nicx pkg list
Display all tracked packages with their package manager and install method.
.TP
.B nicx pkg sync
Install all packages in the tracking list that are not yet present.
Use this on a fresh system to restore your environment:
.PP
.RS
.nf
nicx pkg sync
.fi
.RE
.
.SH GIT SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx git setup
Check that git and gh (GitHub CLI) are installed, verify git identity (user.name,
user.email), confirm gh authentication, and display the configured development directory.
.TP
.B nicx git auth
Run
.B gh auth login
interactively, then configure git to use the gh credential helper.
.TP
.B nicx git status
Show git version, identity, GPG signing status, gh authentication, and tracked repo count.
.TP
.B nicx git add \fIurl\fR
Track a repository by URL (SSH or HTTPS). Parses org and name from the URL and
saves the entry to
.IR ~/.config/nicx/repos.toml .
.TP
.B nicx git remove \fIname\fR
Remove a repository from the tracking list.
.TP
.B nicx git list
List all tracked repositories with their org, URL, and local path.
.TP
.B nicx git clone \fIname\fR
Clone a tracked repository into
.IR devDir/org/name .
If the directory already exists, runs
.B git pull
instead.
.TP
.B nicx git clone-all
Clone all tracked repositories not yet present locally.
.PP
The development directory defaults to
.I ~/Development
and can be overridden in config.toml with
.IR git.dev_dir .
.
.SH GPG SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx gpg setup
Check that gpg is installed. If no secret key is found, prints instructions
for generating one with
.BR "gpg --full-generate-key" .
.TP
.B nicx gpg list
List all available GPG secret keys in long keyid format.
.TP
.B nicx gpg status
Show GPG installation status, git signing key, commit.gpgsign setting,
and the GPG id configured in the pass store.
.TP
.B nicx gpg export \fIkey-id\fR
Export the specified public key in ASCII-armored format to stdout.
.TP
.B nicx gpg import \fIfile\fR
Import a GPG key from the given file.
.
.SH PASS SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx pass setup
Install pass and gpg if missing, initialise the password store with the
configured GPG key, and optionally initialise a git repository inside the store.
.TP
.B nicx pass status
Show whether pass is installed, the store directory, configured GPG id,
git remote, and number of stored passwords.
.TP
.B nicx pass pull
Pull the latest commits from the git remote configured inside the password store.
.TP
.B nicx pass push
Push local commits in the password store to its git remote.
.PP
The GPG key used for the store can be set in config.toml as
.IR pass.gpg_key_id .
The store directory defaults to
.I ~/.password-store
and can be overridden with
.IR pass.store_dir .
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color output (also respected when stdout is not a TTY).
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B nicx
reads its configuration from
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nicx/config.toml
if the XDG variable is set). The file is created with defaults on first run.
.PP
.B Example config.toml:
.PP
.RS
.nf
[output]
color = true
# format = terminal

[system]
# show_swap = true

[git]
# dev_dir = ~/Development
# gh_user =

[pass]
# gpg_key_id =
# store_dir = ~/.password-store
.fi
.RE
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
User configuration file (created with defaults on first run).
.TP
.I ~/.config/nicx/packages.toml
Tracked package list, written by
.BR "nicx pkg install" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/nicx/repos.toml
Tracked repository list, written by
.BR "nicx git add" .
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/nicx
Default install location when using the install script.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/nicx
System-wide install location when using
.BR "make install" .
.
.SH INSTALLATION
Install system-wide from source:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/microservice-tech-nicolas/nicx
cd nicx
make install
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or install to
.I ~/.local/bin
without root:
.PP
.RS
.nf
make install PREFIX=~/.local
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or use the one-line installer:
.PP
.RS
.nf
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/microservice-tech-nicolas/nicx/main/scripts/install.sh | sh
.fi
.RE
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show full system information:
.B nicx system info
.TP
Show help for the system command:
.B nicx help system
.TP
Show version:
.B nicx --version
.
.SH EXTENDING
.B nicx
uses a self-registering command pattern. Adding a new command requires only
creating a new translation unit with a static
.B CommandRegistrar
— no changes to existing infrastructure. See the project README on GitHub for
the developer guide.
.
